Burkina Faso Social Norms Research transcripts

Ramoudane Orou Sannou

01/10/2020

Introduction

This is a summary text analysis of interview and focus group transcripts from the study on social norms related to the registration of births, marriages, and deaths conducted at the HDSS sites of Kaya, Nanoro, and Nouna in Burkina Faso. The analysis provides a typology of the interviewees and reports on the general insights that emerge from the responses given.

Word cloud : most frequent words

Marriage , Naissances and Femme are the most commonly used words. Lets see in what context those words are used by looking at the text that follows the use of each word.

Clearly, in nearly 90% of cases the word femme (woman) is followed by the verb accoucher (to give birth), revealing that women often associate themsevelves with the act of giving birth and not the registration of the new-born. However, one of the sentences containing the word femme refers to women who leave their marital home without informing their husband and probably refers to the risks associated with marriage registration and the reasons for mens reluctance to do it.

The collection of transcripts is likely to be made up of a collection of topics. As such, algorithms can identify topics in a collection of texts and one of the most commonly used algorithm for topic modeling is Latent Dirichlet Allocation.

Since Mariage was the most frequent word across the transcriptions, I am interested in the common themes surrounding that word in the discussions. I will extract all of the sentences that mention the word Mariage, and create a tokenized version of these sentences with stop words removed. I wont perform stemming of the words since this algorithm has limited effect on french words. I will then do LDA on these sentences and review the top words associated with some of the topics.
